1. Accept Payments via API

Use the /payments/initiate endpoint.

Pass customer details, amount, currency, and callback URL.

Receive a transaction ID and redirect URL.

2. Create Payment Links

Go to Dashboard â†’ Payment Links â†’ Create New.

Customize amount, description, expiry, and branding.

Share via SMS, email, or social media.

3. Set Up Webhooks

Navigate to Developer Settings â†’ Webhooks.

Add your endpoint URL.

Choose events (e.g., payment success, failure, refund).

4. Monitor Transactions

Use the dashboard filters to view by date, status, or channel.

Export reports for accounting or analysis.

5. Test in Sandbox Mode

Switch to Sandbox in Developer Settings.

Use test credentials and mock data.

Validate flow before going live.

